description: Ads seemingly advocating for Vice President Kamala Harris on Facebook are really part of an effort by a dark money group to mislead voters. The messages have been viewed millions of times.
title: An Elon Musk-backed political group is posting fake Kamala Harris ads on Facebook

description: Harris is the first vice president to be an alum of a historically Black college, and if she wins, would make history as the first president to be an HBCU graduate.
title: Harris will spend election night at Howard University, the HBCU that helped shape her

description: The discovery of an infected pig at a backyard farm in Oregon raises concerns about bird flu's potential to become a human threat.
title: Bird flu has been found in a pig for the first time in the U.S.

description: About 20 carvings in “a wide range of designs” including some meant to trap demons or to seek help from the Virgin Mary have been found at Gainsborough Old Hall in Lincolnshire, England.
title: ‘Witches marks’ and curses found carved into the walls of historic England manor

description: The NYPD can no longer ticket jaywalkers, after years of protest that enforcement unfairly targeted Black and Hispanic New Yorkers.
title: Enforcement was considered discriminatory. Now New Yorkers can jaywalk legally

description: Depending on who wins the presidential election and the Senate, the conservative supermajority could remain the same, be trimmed or expand to an even larger and more lopsided conservative majority.
title: What could happen at the Supreme Court under Harris and Trump

description: The region drained by the Amazon River, including the Amazon Rainforest, is in the second year of a punishing drought. That has lead to the lowest water levels in more than 100 years for the Amazon and its major tributaries. Millions of people and an array of wildlife depend on those quickly disappearing waters. We travel to the region to see the effects.
title: The World's Largest River is Running Low

description: The U.S. economy grew at an annual rate of 2.8% in the third quarter, led by strong consumer spending. The news comes days before a presidential election in which the economy has been top of mind for many voters.
title: The U.S. economy is growing solidly. Here's what's working — and what's not

description: “There's no need to panic,” an elections expert tells NPR. All but three states have free tracking sites that send updates to voters as their ballot goes through the system.
title: Worried about your 2024 ballot being counted? These states let you track it online

description: Two Yankees fans were ejected from Game 4 of the World Series for trying to pry a ball out of a Dodgers player’s glove. It's a particularly brazen instance of fan interference, but far from the first.
title: Handsy fans disrupted a World Series game. Here are 5 notable MLB interference cases

description: New York Times reporter Ken Bensinger says the America First Policy Institute, which has nearly 300 executive orders ready to be signed, would influence a Trump second term more than Project 2025.
title: How a little-known organization is poised to shape a second Trump administration

description: IV fluids used in hospitals remain in short supply, after Hurricane Helene shut down a key North Carolina factory. The closure has hospitals scrambling to stretch supplies and prioritize care.
title: Shortage of IV fluids leads to canceled surgeries

description: Authorities in the region report at least 62 people have been killed after torrential rain overpowered the area.
title: Spain flooding: Photos show the devastation in Valencia

description: Vice President Harris delivered the closing pitch in her campaign yesterday, reaching out to undecided voters in swing states. And, a look at whether Trump's mass deportation plan is feasible.
title: Harris courts undecided voters. And, is Trump’s mass deportation plan feasible?

description: It sounded like the president was calling Trump supporters "garbage." But the White House said he was talking about a joke made by a comedian at a Trump rally who disparaged Puerto Rico.
title: Biden's 'garbage' remarks give Trump and GOP new fodder on the trail

description: The White House clarified the president's comments, noting that his remarks were directed at a joke made by a comedian who disparaged Puerto Rico.
title: Republicans pounce on Biden's 'garbage' remarks

description: It’s unclear who runs the network of social media accounts that has gotten millions of views amplifying trending claims about alleged voting fraud.
title: A baseless voting claim is being amplified by a network of social media accounts

description: Political prognosticators legally bet over $100 million on the 2024 presidential election, favoring Harris over Trump.
title: Americans bet $100 million on Trump v. Harris, but at what cost?

description: Kids in the greater metro area of Iowa's capital city typically go trick-or-treating the night before Halloween, a tradition that began in the 1930s as a way to help prevent vandalism.
title: Kids in Iowa's capital will trick-or-treat on Halloween for the 1st time since 1938

description: As the nation's first ever indigenous cabinet secretary, Deb Haaland has made it her priority to right the US government's historical wrongs in Indian Country, a monumental task that's not been without controversy.
title: America's first Native American cabinet secretary says she's righting historical wrongs

description: The Aral Sea has nearly disappeared over the last 60 years. Now, its source rivers are depleting.
title: Central Asia’s Ticking Time Bomb: Water

description: Known as the “Festival of Lights,” Diwali is one of the most widely celebrated holidays in India and across the Indian diaspora, including in the U.S. Many celebrate it with food, gifts and fireworks.
title: Millions of people to celebrate Diwali this week. Here is what you should know

description: The world’s longest river is at its lowest levels ever due to devastating drought conditions. The dry conditions in Brazil's Amazon rainforest, have left tributaries and the vital waterway parched, stranding river communities, affecting commerce and livelihoods.
title: Rain is coming, but not enough after punishing Amazon drought

description: The Geneva Conventions recently marked their 75th anniversary, yet the rules of war are being widely violated. NPR’s Greg Myre reports from two ongoing wars, Russia-Ukraine and Israel-Hamas.
title: The rules of war aren't protecting civilians. Can they be enforced?

description: The deck is stacked against election officials online, maybe even more so than in 2020. Conspiracy theories can quickly get millions of views while debunks gather a fraction of the attention.
title: Voting officials face ‘an uphill battle’ to fight election lies

description: NPR sits down with North Carolina pastor Chad Harvey to talk about Donald Trump, religion and politics.
title: Why are some Evangelicals drawn to — and sticking by — Trump? This pastor weighs in

description: Shoppers complain that Starbucks isn't fancy enough — but they also say it's too expensive. The new CEO, Brian Niccol, is ordering up change.
title: Why Starbucks is losing sales, and what it's doing about it

description: A criminal complaint alleges that guards pepper-sprayed Othel Moore Jr., placed a mask over his face and left him in a position that caused him to suffocate.
title: Family releases video of final moments before Black man's death in Missouri prison

description: China declared a “complete success” after it launched a new three-person crew to its space station early Wednesday as the country seeks to expand its exploration of outer space.
title: China launches new crew to its space station as it seeks to expand exploration

description: The order extends a previous one that bars Florida's surgeon general from coercing or intimidating broadcasters that run commercials for an abortion rights amendment.
title: Judge continues to block Florida from threatening TV stations over abortion ads
